[SN]TITLE[SN]
The school teaching Chinese Mandarin

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
From September primary schools across England will have to teach foreign languages.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
4 February 2014 Last updated at 06:29 GMT
Most students will learn European languages like French, German or Spanish - but Nel visited a school where students are learning the Chinese language Mandarin.
More than a billion people speak Mandarin in the world.
The Prime Minister believes learning the Chinese language will help Britain do more business with China.
